<doc id="1002738" wikidata="Q5598854" url="?curid=1002738" title="Great Britain at the 2004 Summer Paralympics">
<text>Great Britain (the name which the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland competes under at Olympic and Paralympic level) sent a delegation of 166 athletes to the [[2004 Summer Paralympics]], covering 15 sports. The ParalympicsGB team entered the opening ceremony behind the Union Flag carried by Noel Thatcher.

==Medallists==

The following British competitors won medals at the Games. In the &#x27;by discipline&#x27; sections below, medallists&#x27; names are in bold.

